public final class EmbededFF
extends Embeded

An internal class for JS Embeded Simulation on FireFox-compatible browsers.

This internal class is only extended internally in JS Simulation Library.

function

protected <T> js.core.JsFunction<T> function(js.Vars<java.lang.String> args)

Creates a JavaScript function.

A function is a fundamental data-type in JavaScript. Note that although functions may be created with this method, this is not efficient, and the preferred way to define functions, in most cases, is to extend Function.

Specified by:
function in class js.Sim
Parameters:
args - A list of the argument values, each naming one or more arguments of the function being created, ended with a string that specifies the body of the function.
Returns:
A newly created function. Invoking it executes the JavaScript code specified by last string value of the variable argument args.
Throws:
java.lang.RuntimeException - JavaScript throws a SyntaxError if there was a JavaScript syntax error in one of the value of the variable arguments. See Js.err(Object) and JsSyntaxError for JS Simulation.
Since:
1.0
See Also:
Function
